{"key":"post-13528655","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13528655</id>\n<content>I think some of you don't realize that the boiling of grains is not to hydrate them.&amp;nbsp; They should be fully hydrated when you boil or they'll burst.&amp;nbsp; Boiling is to heat them up, so they steam dry afterward before loading into jars.&amp;nbsp; This prevents over-wet grain jars which perform poorly if at all.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13528746</next>\n<prev>13528616</prev>\n<first>13488594</first>\n<last>13532549</last>\n<when>1290527538</when>\n<utime>11/23/10 05:52 PM</utime>\n</post>"}